    <fr:title text="Higher duploid theory">Higher duploid theory</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Project</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A project to explore the category theory of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/munch-2014.xml" title="Models of a non-associative composition" addr="munch-2014" type="local">duploids</fr:link> and their higher-dimensional generalizations.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" hidden-when-empty="true">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors />
        <fr:title text="References">References</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/guillaumemunch.xml" title="Guillaume Munch-Maccagnoni" addr="guillaumemunch" type="local">Guillaume Munch-Maccagnoni</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2014</fr:year>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>munch-2014</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/munch-2014.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Models of a non-associative composition">Models of a non-associative composition</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Reference</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="doi">10.1007/978-3-642-54830-7_26</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>We characterise the polarised evaluation order through a categorical structure where the hypothesis that composition is associative is relaxed. Duploid is the name of the structure, as a reference to Jean-Louis Loday’s duplicial algebras. The main result is a reflection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\textit {Adj}\to \textit {Dupl}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\textit {Dupl}]]></fr:tex> is a category of duploids and duploid functors, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\textit {Adj}]]></fr:tex> is the category of adjunctions and pseudo maps of adjunctions. The result suggests that the various biases in denotational semantics: indirect, call-by-value, call-by-name… are a way of hiding the fact that composition is not always associative.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
